}
@article{Liu2010,
abstract = {Smoking is a leading global cause of disease and mortality. We established the Oxford-GlaxoSmithKline study (Ox-GSK) to perform a genome-wide meta-analysis of SNP association with smoking-related behavioral traits. Our final data set included 41,150 individuals drawn from 20 disease, population and control cohorts. Our analysis confirmed an effect on smoking quantity at a locus on 15q25 (P = 9.45 x 10(-19)) that includes CHRNA5, CHRNA3 and CHRNB4, three genes encoding neuronal nicotinic acetylcholine receptor subunits. We used data from the 1000 Genomes project to investigate the region using imputation, which allowed for analysis of virtually all common SNPs in the region and offered a fivefold increase in marker density over HapMap2 (ref. 2) as an imputation reference panel. Our fine-mapping approach identified a SNP showing the highest significance, rs55853698, located within the promoter region of CHRNA5. Conditional analysis also identified a secondary locus (rs6495308) in CHRNA3.},
author = {Liu, Jason Z and Tozzi, Federica and Waterworth, Dawn M and Pillai, Sreekumar G and Muglia, Pierandrea and Middleton, Lefkos and Berrettini, Wade and Knouff, Christopher W and Yuan, Xin and Waeber, G{\'{e}}rard and Vollenweider, Peter and Preisig, Martin and Wareham, Nicholas J and Zhao, Jing Hua and Loos, Ruth J F and Barroso, In{\^{e}}s and Khaw, Kay-Tee and Grundy, Scott and Barter, Philip and Mahley, Robert and Kesaniemi, Antero and McPherson, Ruth and Vincent, John B and Strauss, John and Kennedy, James L and Farmer, Anne and McGuffin, Peter and Day, Richard and Matthews, Keith and Bakke, Per and Gulsvik, Amund and Lucae, Susanne and Ising, Marcus and Brueckl, Tanja and Horstmann, Sonja and Wichmann, H-Erich and Rawal, Rajesh and Dahmen, Norbert and Lamina, Claudia and Polasek, Ozren and Zgaga, Lina and Huffman, Jennifer and Campbell, Susan and Kooner, Jaspal and Chambers, John C and Burnett, Mary Susan and Devaney, Joseph M and Pichard, Augusto D and Kent, Kenneth M and Satler, Lowell and Lindsay, Joseph M and Waksman, Ron and Epstein, Stephen and Wilson, James F and Wild, Sarah H and Campbell, Harry and Vitart, Veronique and Reilly, Muredach P and Li, Mingyao and Qu, Liming and Wilensky, Robert and Matthai, William and Hakonarson, Hakon H and Rader, Daniel J and Franke, Andre and Wittig, Michael and Sch{\"{a}}fer, Arne and Uda, Manuela and Terracciano, Antonio and Xiao, Xiangjun and Busonero, Fabio and Scheet, Paul and Schlessinger, David and Clair, David St and Rujescu, Dan and Abecasis, Gon{\c{c}}alo R and Grabe, Hans J{\"{o}}rgen and Teumer, Alexander and V{\"{o}}lzke, Henry and Petersmann, Astrid and John, Ulrich and Rudan, Igor and Hayward, Caroline and Wright, Alan F and Kolcic, Ivana and Wright, Benjamin J and Thompson, John R and Balmforth, Anthony J and Hall, Alistair S and Samani, Nilesh J and Anderson, Carl A and Ahmad, Tariq and Mathew, Christopher G and Parkes, Miles and Satsangi, Jack and Caulfield, Mark and Munroe, Patricia B and Farr